WEBVTT

00:05.657 --> 00:07.746
PREVIOUSLY
ON "PUSHING DAISIES"...

00:07.790 --> 00:10.532
CHARLOTTE'S FATHER, MY LOVER,
WAS VIVIAN'S FIANCE.

00:10.575 --> 00:12.534
VIVIAN CAN NEVER KNOW.

00:12.577 --> 00:15.493
DWIGHT DIXON. I WAS A FRIEND
OF YOUR FATHER'S 25 YEARS AGO.

00:15.537 --> 00:17.104
I'M ACTUALLY
TRYING TO FIND HIM.

00:17.147 --> 00:18.366
I'M AFRAID WE LOST TOUCH.

00:18.409 --> 00:20.368
I-I'M RALSTON.
THIS IS MAURICE.

00:20.411 --> 00:23.197
Chuck: THEY HAVE YOUR EYEBROWS,
AND THEY DO PARLOR MAGIC!

00:23.240 --> 00:26.026
PEOPLE LOOSEN UP, DROP THEIR
BAGGAGE, AND LIVE A LITTLE.

00:26.069 --> 00:28.854
HI, I'M NED. I THOUGHT
I'D STOP BY BECAUSE...

00:28.898 --> 00:30.813
BASICALLY,
WE HAVE THE SAME DAD.

00:42.477 --> 00:45.567
Narrator: AT THIS VERY MOMENT
IN THE TOWN OF COEUR D'COEURS,

00:45.610 --> 00:48.439
YOUNG NED BELIEVED IN MAGIC.

00:48.483 --> 00:51.225
IT WAS NOT THE MAGIC
THAT SPARKED FROM HIS FINGERTIP

00:51.268 --> 00:54.097
WHEN HE TOUCHED A DEAD THING
ALIVE AGAIN.

00:54.141 --> 00:57.666
THAT PARTICULAR MAGIC
HAD NOT YET BEEN DISCOVERED.

00:57.709 --> 01:01.104
THIS WAS THE MAGIC
OF A FATHER'S LOVE.

01:01.148 --> 01:03.933
[ DIGBY WHINES ]

01:03.976 --> 01:08.242
YOUNG NED WOULD DISCOVER
THIS MAGIC WAS NOT MAGIC AT ALL.

01:08.285 --> 01:09.460
ALAKAZAM!

01:09.504 --> 01:11.114
Narrator:
IT WAS JUST A TRICK.

01:11.158 --> 01:13.116
AFTER NED'S MOTHER DIED,

01:13.160 --> 01:15.597
HIS FATHER PERFORMED
ANOTHER TRICK --

01:15.640 --> 01:18.165
A CRUEL DISAPPEARING ACT.

01:18.208 --> 01:20.080
I'LL BE BACK.

01:20.123 --> 01:22.821
Narrator: AND WHEN HIS FATHER
NEVER CAME BACK,

01:22.865 --> 01:25.955
NED STOPPED BELIEVING IN MAGIC.

01:25.998 --> 01:28.784
YOUNG NED DISCOVERED
HIS FATHER WOULD ONE DAY

01:28.827 --> 01:31.526
PERFORM HIS SLEIGHTS OF HAND
AND MISDIRECTIONS

01:31.569 --> 01:34.616
FOR A YOUNGER,
MORE IMPRESSIONABLE AUDIENCE,

01:34.659 --> 01:37.053
A NEW FAMILY
THAT DID NOT INCLUDE NED,

01:37.097 --> 01:39.360
BUT DID INCLUDE
HIS HALF-BROTHERS,

01:39.403 --> 01:41.492
MAURICE AND RALSTON.

01:41.536 --> 01:43.799
MAURICE AND RALSTON
LOVED THEIR FATHER

01:43.842 --> 01:45.801
AND DELIGHTED
IN HIS MAGICAL TRICKS

01:45.844 --> 01:48.760
AND INSISTED ON LEARNING
EVERY ONE OF THEM.

01:51.502 --> 01:54.288
BUT THERE WAS ONE MAGIC TRICK
THEIR FATHER NEVER TAUGHT THEM

01:54.331 --> 01:56.594
AND WOULD ONLY SHOW THEM ONCE --

01:56.638 --> 01:59.684
A CRUEL DISAPPEARING ACT.

01:59.728 --> 02:05.081
IT'S 19 YEARS, 42 WEEKS, 6 DAYS,
13 HOURS, AND 7 MINUTES LATER.

02:05.125 --> 02:06.648
MAURICE AND RALSTON

02:06.691 --> 02:09.868
HAVE BECOME THE ILLUSIONIST DUO
"TWO FOR THE SHOW."

02:09.912 --> 02:13.045
THE MERCURIAL WORLD OF MAGIC
AND ITS ASSOCIATIONS

02:13.089 --> 02:15.700
HAD ANOTHER EFFECT
ON HALF-BROTHER NED,

02:15.744 --> 02:17.006
WHO COULD WAKE THE DEAD...

02:17.049 --> 02:18.050
MAGICIANS?

02:18.094 --> 02:19.530
ILLUSIONISTS. ILLUSIONISTS.

02:19.574 --> 02:21.663
Narrator:
AT THE MERE MENTION OF MAGIC,

02:21.706 --> 02:26.233
HE EXPERIENCED THE STING
OF ANXIETY-INDUCED ACID REFLUX.

02:26.276 --> 02:28.017
WHO DOESN'T LIKE MAGIC?

02:28.060 --> 02:30.193
I-I LOVE MAGIC...

02:30.237 --> 02:32.587
AS MUCH AS I LOVE OTHER FORMS
OF POPULAR ENTERTAINMENT,

02:32.630 --> 02:34.589
LIKE BOXARATE TAE-KILL-DO
CAGE-FIGHTING

02:34.632 --> 02:36.330
OR MONSTER TRUCKS ON ICE.

02:36.373 --> 02:38.419
TO CERTAIN FACTIONS
OF THE GOD-FEARING PUBLIC,

02:38.462 --> 02:41.378
MAGIC IS THE DEVIL'S WORK,
YOU LITTLE DEVILS.

02:41.422 --> 02:43.380
MAGICALLY DELICIOUS
LITTLE DEVILS.

02:43.424 --> 02:44.860
MNH-MNH.

02:44.903 --> 02:46.166
OH, I THOUGHT YOU WERE --

02:46.209 --> 02:48.037
MAGICALLY DELICIOUS
LITTLE DEVILS.

02:48.080 --> 02:50.431
MM-HMM.
LIKE A CONFECTION.

02:50.474 --> 02:53.521
INSIDE ONE OF THESE PIES
IS A PRIZE.

02:53.564 --> 02:56.045
BUT WHICH ONE?
THIS PIE? THAT PIE?

02:56.088 --> 02:57.481
PICK A PIE, ANY PIE.

02:57.525 --> 02:59.091
OOH, THAT ONE!
THAT ONE!

03:03.400 --> 03:05.446
YOU JUST MAGICALLY JULIENNED
THE CHERRIES.

03:05.489 --> 03:08.275
BUT WAIT, THERE'S MORE.

03:08.318 --> 03:10.407
OH! A MAGIC SHOW!OH! A MAGIC SHOW!

03:10.451 --> 03:11.974
A MAGIC SHOW?!

03:12.017 --> 03:14.672
WHERE DID I PUT THAT RAT'S ASS
I COULD GIVE?

03:14.716 --> 03:16.979
MAGIC AIN'T NOTHING
BUT A VOODOO GRIFT.

03:17.022 --> 03:19.111
MAGIC IS AS MAGICAL
AS YOU WANT IT TO BE.

03:19.155 --> 03:21.810
YEAH. HE MAGICALLY PUT
THOSE TICKETS IN THAT PIE.

03:21.853 --> 03:24.769
IF BY "MAGICALLY," YOU MEAN
"MADE YOU LOOK THAT WAY

03:24.813 --> 03:26.467
SO YOU WOULDN'T SEE
WHAT THEY WERE DOING THIS WAY,"

03:26.510 --> 03:28.730
THEN, YES, THOSE TICKETS
ALAKAZAMMED THEIR WAY

03:28.773 --> 03:31.472
RIGHT UNDERNEATH
THAT DELICIOUS, FLAKY CRUST.

03:31.515 --> 03:34.692
OR HOCUS PULLED THE DAMN TICKETS
OUT OF HIS POCKET

03:34.736 --> 03:36.868
AND POCUS SLID THEM
UNDER THE PIE PAN,

03:36.912 --> 03:39.001
AS EVIDENCED BY
THE CHERRY-RHUBARB CRUMBLE

03:39.044 --> 03:41.003
ON HIS SLEEVE.

03:41.046 --> 03:42.526
WE'RE PERFORMING
AFTER THE SECOND PERFORMANCE

03:42.570 --> 03:44.006
OF THE GREAT HERRMANN.

03:44.049 --> 03:46.487
HE'S THE BIG, MUCKETY-MUCK
PATRIARCH

03:46.530 --> 03:48.489
OF THE CONJURER'S CASTLE,
AND TO US, TOO.

03:48.532 --> 03:49.881
AFTER DAD HAD TO LEAVE...

03:49.925 --> 03:51.143
"HAD TO LEAVE"?

03:51.187 --> 03:52.841
WHY ELSE
WOULD HE HAVE LEFT?

03:52.884 --> 03:54.364
AFTER DAD HAD TO LEAVE,

03:54.408 --> 03:56.061
HERRMANN WAS
THE NEXT BEST THING.

03:56.105 --> 03:59.108
YAY. ANOTHER MAGIC DAD.

03:59.151 --> 04:02.198
WE'LL INTRODUCE YOU AFTER THE
SHOW, IF YOU COME TO THE SHOW.

04:02.242 --> 04:03.634
WILL YOU COME TO THE SHOW,
BIG BROTHER?

04:03.678 --> 04:06.507
BIG HALF-BROTHER,
ONCE REMOVED BY THE FACT

04:06.550 --> 04:08.596
THAT YOU DIDN'T KNOW I EXISTED
UNTIL LAST WEEK.

04:08.639 --> 04:11.990
I'D LIKE TO RSVP
IN THE RESOUNDINGLY AFFIRMATIVE.

04:12.034 --> 04:13.949
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
MAGIC WAS A VOODOO GRIFT.

04:13.992 --> 04:15.646
IT IS A VOODOO GRIFT.

04:15.690 --> 04:18.388
BUT EXPOSING THESE TWO
AND THEIR FAIRY-DUST DECEPTIONS

04:18.432 --> 04:20.347
WILL ONLY HONE
MY P.I. SKILLS,

04:20.390 --> 04:22.740
MUCH LIKE A BRAINTEASER
OR "WHERE'S WALDO?"

04:22.784 --> 04:24.481
YOU'RE NOT INVITED
IF YOU'RE GONNA HECKLE.

04:24.525 --> 04:26.091
BUT SHAZAM --

04:26.135 --> 04:27.571
I HAVE A TICKET.

04:27.615 --> 04:30.226
I'LL BE THERE, FRONT AND CENTER,
LOUD AND APPLAUDING,

04:30.270 --> 04:32.663
SNAPPING LIKE A BEATNIK
OR PRAISING THE LORD --
WHATEVER YOU'D LIKE.

04:32.707 --> 04:34.317
LOUD AND APPLAUDING!
LOUD AND APPLAUDING!

04:34.361 --> 04:36.014
AND PREFERABLY AMAZED.

04:36.058 --> 04:38.539
WHAT DO YOU SAY,
FRERE PIE MAKER?

04:38.582 --> 04:41.455
LOOK! THERE'S A TICKET
WITH YOUR NAME ON IT.

04:41.498 --> 04:42.456
OH!

04:45.067 --> 04:47.069
[ LIGHT MUSIC PLAYS ]

04:53.118 --> 04:54.511
[ LIGHT APPLAUSE ]

04:59.908 --> 05:01.953
YOU BARELY SAID
A WORD TO THEM.

05:01.997 --> 05:03.912
I BARELY KNOW THEM.
I SAW THEM ONCE WHEN I WAS 9,

05:03.955 --> 05:05.348
AND THEY WERE JUST
THOSE LITTLE BASTARDS

05:05.392 --> 05:07.045
MY FATHER WAS
CHEATING ON ME WITH.

05:07.089 --> 05:09.047
THOSE LITTLE BASTARDS
ARE NOW YOUR LITTLE BROTHERS.

05:09.091 --> 05:11.049
YOU CAN'T JUST FLASH
SOME JAZZ HANDS

05:11.093 --> 05:12.921
AND THEN ABRACADABRA --
BROTHERLY LOVE.

05:12.964 --> 05:14.792
WHAT HE SAID. THERE SHOULD
BE A GRACE PERIOD,

05:14.836 --> 05:16.141
THEN A GETTING-TO-KNOW-YOU
PERIOD,

05:16.185 --> 05:17.882
THEN A DINNER
ON A NATIONAL HOLIDAY.

05:17.926 --> 05:20.668
I INVITE THEM TO THE PIE HOLE,
AND SUDDENLY IT'S,

05:20.711 --> 05:23.018
"FRERE PIE MAKER,
COME TO OUR SHOW."

05:23.061 --> 05:24.846
IT'S A MAGIC SHOW.

05:24.889 --> 05:26.587
WHAT DO YOU GOT
AGAINST A MAGIC SHOW?

05:26.630 --> 05:29.372
THERE'S SEQUINS AND DRAMA
AND THE PROMISE OF BLOODSHED.

05:29.416 --> 05:31.679
NEXT TO PAGEANTS,
THEY'RE MY FAVORITE THING.

05:31.722 --> 05:33.376
THEY GIVE ME ACID REFLUX.

05:33.420 --> 05:36.074
OH, HERE. SUCK A LOZENGE.

05:36.118 --> 05:37.511
A MAGICAL LOZENGE
THAT'LL MAKE ME FORGET

05:37.554 --> 05:39.034
THEY'RE PUTTING ON
A MAGIC SHOW,

05:39.077 --> 05:40.601
WHICH IS THE SAME KIND OF SHOW
MY DAD PUT ON,

05:40.644 --> 05:42.342
SO WHAT THEY'RE PULLING
OUT OF THEIR MAGIC HATS

05:42.385 --> 05:44.126
ISN'T A RABBIT --
IT'S MY CHILDHOOD TRAUMA.

05:44.169 --> 05:46.520
THEY'RE WEARING IT LIKE A CAPE
AND TAKING IT TO THE STAGE.

05:49.523 --> 05:51.263
[ GULPING ]

05:51.307 --> 05:53.527
HERE I WAS JUST ABOUT TO TELL
Y'ALL TO SHUT THE HELL UP,

05:53.570 --> 05:55.703
AND THEN YOU STOPPED TALKING
SO I DIDN'T HAVE TO.

05:55.746 --> 05:57.922
MAURICE AND RALSTON ARE
THE FAMILY THAT YOU
DIDN'T KNOW YOU HAD.

05:57.966 --> 05:59.533
IF I COULD
TALK TO MY AUNT LILY

05:59.576 --> 06:01.622
AS THE MOTHER
I DIDN'T KNOW I HAD...

06:01.665 --> 06:04.059
OH, I'D HAVE
A SEA OF QUESTIONS.

06:04.102 --> 06:06.627
DON'T YOU HAVE
A SEA OF QUESTIONS?

06:06.670 --> 06:08.368
THERE MAY BE A POND.

06:08.411 --> 06:10.544
THEN DIVE IN.

06:10.587 --> 06:12.589
I'M NOT A DIVER.
I'M A CAUTIOUS SWIMMER.

06:12.633 --> 06:14.635
I TEST THE WATER
WITH MY BIG TOE

06:14.678 --> 06:16.941
AND THEN GENTLY WADE
INTO THE SHALLOWS.

06:16.985 --> 06:18.595
Narrator:
WHILE THE PIE MAKER INSISTED

06:18.639 --> 06:21.729
ON WADING INTO THE SHALLOWS
OF BROTHERLY LOVE,

06:21.772 --> 06:24.035
CHUCK INSISTED
ON DIVING INTO THE DEPTHS

06:24.079 --> 06:27.299
OF A RECENT
AND STRANGE REVELATION.

06:27.343 --> 06:31.042
HER AUNT LILY WAS, IN FACT,
HER MOTHER LILY.

06:31.086 --> 06:35.699
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]
NOT SATISFIED HEARING SUCH
LIFE-ALTERING NEWS SECONDHAND,

06:35.743 --> 06:39.442
CHUCK WANTED TO HEAR THE WORDS
DIRECTLY FROM HER MOTHER'S LIPS.

06:39.486 --> 06:41.749
HELLO?

06:41.792 --> 06:44.752
Chuck: [ British accent ]
Oh, hello, I'm from
Livelong Day Life Insurance.

06:44.795 --> 06:47.450
NOW, WE HAVE AN AMAZING
MOTHER'S DAY OFFER

06:47.494 --> 06:49.757
FOR WOMEN WHO HAVE
GIVEN BIRTH.

06:49.800 --> 06:52.063
NOW, MAY I ASK,
DO YOU QUALIFY FOR --

06:52.107 --> 06:53.935
[ Click, dial tone ]

06:53.978 --> 06:57.155
[ French accent ] Our November
cheese is rubbed with paprika.

06:57.199 --> 07:00.507
IT IS PARTICULARLY
APPEALING TO, UH,

07:00.550 --> 07:03.292
THE WOMAN
WHO HAS HAD A BABY?

07:03.335 --> 07:05.294
HAVE YOU EVER HAD A BABY?

07:05.337 --> 07:06.904
[ Click, dial tone ]

07:06.948 --> 07:08.776
[ Southern accent ]
YOU'VE BEEN RANDOMLY SELECTED

07:08.819 --> 07:10.473
TO RECEIVE YOUR VERY OWN
PSYCHIC READING.

07:10.517 --> 07:11.648
[ CLICK ]

07:11.692 --> 07:12.910
HELLO?

07:12.954 --> 07:13.911
[ Dial tone ]

07:15.565 --> 07:17.001
OH, NO.

07:17.045 --> 07:19.351
HERE COMES
ANOTHER MAGIC DAD.

07:19.395 --> 07:20.875
Chuck: IS THAT
THE GREAT HERRMANN?

07:20.918 --> 07:22.877
MAYBE HE COULD BE
YOUR MAGIC DAD, TOO.

07:22.920 --> 07:26.141
ALREADY HAD A MAGIC DAD.
IT DIDN'T WORK OUT.

07:26.184 --> 07:27.751
I NEED ANOTHER LOZENGE.

07:34.758 --> 07:37.108
LOZENGE ISN'T WORKING.
STOMACH ACID'S RISING...

07:37.152 --> 07:39.502
AS WELL AS OTHER CONTENTS
OF STOMACH.

07:39.546 --> 07:41.286
ARE YOU THE PIE MAKER?

07:41.330 --> 07:43.158
I'M A PIE MAKER.

07:43.201 --> 07:46.074
HELLO!
EXCUSE ME, EXCUSE ME.

07:46.117 --> 07:48.293
I FEEL I SHOULD HUG YOU.
CAN I GIVE YOU A BIG HUG?

07:48.337 --> 07:50.818
I'M ALREADY HUGGING, AND THERE'S
NOTHING YOU CAN DO ABOUT IT.

07:50.861 --> 07:51.993
I WANT A HUG!

07:52.036 --> 07:53.473
I'M NOT MADE OF HUGS.

07:53.516 --> 07:56.301
MAURICE AND RALSTON
CAN'T STOP GUSHING.

07:56.345 --> 07:58.782
I'M SO GRATEFUL
THAT YOU CAME INTO THEIR LIVES.

07:58.826 --> 08:00.218
PERHAPS YOU CAN
TAKE SOME HEAT OFF ME.

08:00.262 --> 08:01.916
THE BOYS ARE RATHER NEEDY.

08:01.959 --> 08:03.570
WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT LATER.

08:03.613 --> 08:06.398
PRETTY GIRL,
PRETTY GIRL, AND YOU...

08:06.442 --> 08:10.533
I SENSE YOU'RE A GREAT
INVESTIGATOR OF THINGS UNSOLVED.

08:10.577 --> 08:12.840
NAMED AFTER A POET AND A FISH.

08:12.883 --> 08:15.407
MM-HMM. I SENSE YOU BETTER
GIVE ME BACK MY WALLET

08:15.451 --> 08:16.757
'FORE I MAKE MY FOOT
DISAPPEAR UP YOUR --

08:16.800 --> 08:18.846
THE BOYS TELL ME
YOU'RE A HECKLER.

08:18.889 --> 08:21.283
WE DON'T PLAY THAT WAY
AT THE CONJURER'S CASTLE,

08:21.326 --> 08:23.633
SO LET'S NIP THAT IN THE BUD,
SHALL WE?

08:23.677 --> 08:27.245
OH, YEAH? AND HOW DO YOU
PROPOSE WE NIP, HERMAN?

08:27.289 --> 08:29.247
IT'S HERRMANN.

08:29.291 --> 08:31.119
AND THIS IS HOW WE NIP.

08:31.162 --> 08:33.687
EVER HAD YOUR BREATH TAKEN,
EMERSON COD?

08:33.730 --> 08:36.428
LEACHED FROM YOUR LUNGS
BY A CEMENT MASS

08:36.472 --> 08:38.692
CRUSHING YOU
IN A DEADLY EMBRACE?

08:38.735 --> 08:39.736
NO.

08:39.780 --> 08:41.259
IN JUST MOMENTS,

08:41.303 --> 08:43.784
I WILL BE CONTORTING MY SHACKLED
BODY INTO THIS BOX,

08:43.827 --> 08:45.350
WHICH WILL THEN BE FILLED

08:45.394 --> 08:47.788
WITH QUICK 'N' HARD BRAND
QUICK-SET CEMENT

08:47.831 --> 08:49.833
AND THEN WELDED SHUT.

08:49.877 --> 08:53.576
DEMENTED AND CEMENTED,
I GIVE YOU "CEMENTIA!"

08:53.620 --> 08:54.882
[ LAUGHS ]

08:54.925 --> 08:56.797
IF MY SHACKLES ARE SECURE,
MR. COD,

08:56.840 --> 09:00.235
THEN KINDLY RETURN
TO THE AUDIENCE.

09:00.278 --> 09:01.628
[ CHAINS RATTLE ]

09:01.671 --> 09:03.847
AH, APPLAUSE FOR EMERSON COD!

09:03.891 --> 09:05.327
[ APPLAUSE ]

09:05.370 --> 09:06.633
[ CLANK ]

09:06.676 --> 09:08.591
NOW YOU SEE ME...

09:13.683 --> 09:15.076
[ APPLAUSE ]

09:22.257 --> 09:23.693
[ AUDIENCE MURMURS ]

09:26.391 --> 09:28.045
EMERSON COD.

09:28.089 --> 09:30.178
IT WAS NO ACCIDENT
I CHOSE YOU TO VOLUNTEER.

09:30.221 --> 09:32.963
I REQUIRE YOUR KEEN EYE
AND INVESTIGATION OF THINGS

09:33.007 --> 09:34.182
IN A PERSONAL MATTER.

09:34.225 --> 09:36.793
SOMEONE HAS BEEN KILLING
MY ASSISTANTS.

09:36.837 --> 09:39.883
I INVITE YOU TONIGHT
TO SOLVE THEIR MURDERS.

09:41.755 --> 09:43.670
I LIVE TO AMAZE ANOTHER DAY!

09:45.062 --> 09:48.109
Narrator:
BUT NOT ANOTHER DAY AFTER THAT.

09:54.158 --> 09:55.725
HER NAME WAS ALICE.

09:55.769 --> 09:58.249
TONIGHT WOULD'VE BEEN OUR 200th
PERFORMANCE TOGETHER.

09:58.293 --> 10:00.338
I FOUND HER JUST LIKE THIS...

10:00.382 --> 10:02.297
EXCEPT OVER THERE.

10:02.340 --> 10:04.647
YOU TURNED YOUR ASSISTANT
INTO A BUNNY?

10:04.691 --> 10:06.780
MY ASSISTANT
HAS ALWAYS BEEN A BUNNY.

10:06.823 --> 10:09.652
OH, I-I JUST WANTED TO SEE
IF HE KNEW THAT.

10:09.696 --> 10:12.829
ALICE WAS MURDERED
LIKE THE OTHERS.

10:12.873 --> 10:14.526
FRED AND GINGER WERE IMPALED

10:14.570 --> 10:16.616
WHEN A RIGGING IN MY COAT
MISFIRED.

10:16.659 --> 10:18.400
THEY WOULD FLY OUT OF MY POCKETS

10:18.443 --> 10:20.924
IN A PUFF
OF GLITTER AND BIRDSEED

10:20.968 --> 10:24.058
AS I STRUMMED
A CHIRPING SLIDE GUITAR.

10:24.101 --> 10:26.538
AND MERCURY, SWEET MERCURY.

10:26.582 --> 10:29.933
MERCURY LOVED PERFORMING
WITH BALLOONS AND CHILDREN.

10:29.977 --> 10:32.022
THAT'S WHEN HE WAS
HAPPIEST OF ALL.

10:32.066 --> 10:36.070
AND NOW HE'S DEAD,
BLUDGEONED BY A FALLING SANDBAG.

10:36.113 --> 10:38.202
WHO WOULD WANT TO KILL
ALL YOUR ANIMALS?

10:38.246 --> 10:41.031
[ EMERSON CLEARS THROAT ]
WHILE WE CAN APPRECIATE
AND SYMPATHIZE

10:41.075 --> 10:42.946
WITH YOUR PREDICAMENT,
MISTER HERRMANN...

10:42.990 --> 10:44.426
PLEASE, CALL ME GREAT.

10:44.469 --> 10:45.993
NO.

10:46.036 --> 10:48.125
...WE'RE PRIVATE DETECTIVES,
NOT PET DETECTIVES.

10:48.169 --> 10:50.693
IT WOULD SULLY MY REPUTATION
AS AN EXPERT IN THE FIELD

10:50.737 --> 10:52.347
IF I WERE TO TAKE
TO INVESTIGATING

10:52.390 --> 10:55.263
MISSING "PUDDY TATS"
OR DEAD "BUNNY WABBITS."

10:55.306 --> 10:56.917
I WANT TO HELP MISSING PUDDIES
AND DEAD BUNNIES.

10:56.960 --> 10:58.658
EH.I'M CURIOUS --

10:58.701 --> 11:02.183
DO PET DETECTIVES GET PAID MORE
THAN THE OTHER KIND?

11:02.226 --> 11:04.359
PET DETECTIVES GET PAID
A WHOLE LOT MORE,

11:04.402 --> 11:06.578
SO YOU NEED TO GET
TO PRESTIDIGITATING

11:06.622 --> 11:09.016
A LITTLE MORE GREEN
IF YOU WANT TO GET SERIOUS.

11:13.673 --> 11:14.935
BLOW ON MY HANDS.

11:14.978 --> 11:18.939
MAN, GIVE ME MY DAMN MONEY.

11:18.982 --> 11:19.983
[ OLIVE GASPS ]

11:20.027 --> 11:22.159
OH!THAT WAS GREAT!

11:22.203 --> 11:23.944
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,

11:23.987 --> 11:27.861
THE COUNTY BRIDGE AND TUNNEL
FOLK HAVE ARRIVED FOR THE 9:00.

11:29.123 --> 11:30.602
UM, GREAT?

11:30.646 --> 11:32.996
UH, I NEVER GOT TO ASK --

11:33.040 --> 11:35.433
HOW EXACTLY DO YOU KNOW
MAURICE AND RALSTON?

11:35.477 --> 11:37.435
I WAS THERE
WHEN THEIR FATHER LEFT --

11:37.479 --> 11:38.915
YOUR FATHER LEFT.

11:38.959 --> 11:40.525
I HAD REAL GOOD SEATS
TO THAT SHOW.

11:40.569 --> 11:43.050
I WAS THE DRESS REHEARSAL.
THE SHOW SUCKED THEN.

11:43.093 --> 11:45.530
WHAT DO YOU TELL A COUPLE
OF KIDS YOU'VE NEVER MET

11:45.574 --> 11:46.967
THAT THEIR DAD,
WHO YOU'VE NEVER MET,

11:47.010 --> 11:48.751
HAS JUST DROPPED THEM
LIKE THEY WERE HOT?

11:48.795 --> 11:50.231
YOU CAN'T SUGARCOAT
THAT TURD.

11:50.274 --> 11:52.407
NO, NOT EFFECTIVELY.
WHAT DID YOU TELL THEM?

11:52.450 --> 11:53.713
WHAT THEY WANTED
TO HEAR --

11:53.756 --> 11:55.105
THAT THEIR DAD
WAS AN IMPORTANT MAN

11:55.149 --> 11:58.021
WITH IMPORTANT-MAN MATTERS
TO ATTEND TO.

11:58.065 --> 12:02.025
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.
PLEASE STOP CRYING. BLAH.

12:02.069 --> 12:05.681
DID THEIR DA--
MY DAD SAY ANYTHING TO YOU?

12:05.725 --> 12:07.117
WHAT WAS HE GONNA SAY?

12:07.161 --> 12:09.032
"HEY, THE BOYS WILL BE
HUNGRY IN AN HOUR"?

12:09.076 --> 12:11.687
HE WAS DITCHING THE KIDS
AT A SUNDAY MATINEE,

12:11.731 --> 12:13.123
FOR CHRISTMAS' SAKE.

12:13.167 --> 12:15.647
THANKS FOR LOOKING OUT
FOR THEM.

12:15.691 --> 12:17.214
DIDN'T HAVE
ANY OTHER CHOICE.

12:17.258 --> 12:19.782
EVERY DAY AFTER SCHOOL,
THEY'D POP BY

12:19.826 --> 12:21.784
LOOKING TO BE TAUGHT
SOME NEW MAGIC TRICK

12:21.828 --> 12:23.307
OR PLAY WITH MY MONKEY.

12:23.351 --> 12:24.744
HEED THIS WARNING --

12:24.787 --> 12:28.269
ESTABLISH VERY CLEAR BOUNDARIES
EARLY AND OFTEN.

12:28.312 --> 12:31.359
I GUESS THEY JUST NEEDED
A FATHER.

12:31.402 --> 12:35.667
SON... EVER FEED A STRAY
PUSSYCAT? IT WAS LIKE THAT.

12:35.711 --> 12:38.192
YOU LOVE THE PUSSYCAT,
AND I DO LOVE THOSE BOYS,

12:38.235 --> 12:41.673
BUT THAT PLATE OF TASTY PATE
WITH THE TUNA SAUCE

12:41.717 --> 12:45.068
WAS NOT A PROMISE.

12:45.112 --> 12:47.505
Narrator: IT WAS THE PROMISE
OF SISTERLY DEVOTION

12:47.549 --> 12:49.029
THAT CONCERNED LILY.

12:49.072 --> 12:52.728
30 YEARS, 9 MONTHS AGO,
LILY BROKE THAT PROMISE

12:52.772 --> 12:56.863
WHEN SHE WAS IMPREGNATED
BY HER SISTER VIVIAN'S FIANCE.

12:56.906 --> 12:58.473
LILY LIVED IN FEAR

12:58.516 --> 13:00.954
THAT ONE DAY VIVIAN
WOULD DISCOVER HER BETRAYAL

13:00.997 --> 13:02.782
AND SETTLE HER HASH,

13:02.825 --> 13:06.873
AND TODAY THAT HASH-SETTLING DAY
HAS COME ONE DAY CLOSER.

13:06.916 --> 13:07.874
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

13:09.527 --> 13:11.094
[ GUN COCKS ]

13:11.138 --> 13:12.704
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

13:12.748 --> 13:16.186
Narrator: WHO THE HELL HE WAS,
WAS DWIGHT DIXON.

13:16.230 --> 13:19.711
IN HIS YOUTH, DWIGHT DIXON
BRANDISHED THE BLUE BERET

13:19.755 --> 13:22.236
OF THE UNITED NATIONS
PEACEKEEPERS.

13:22.279 --> 13:25.369
TOGETHER WITH CHUCK'S FATHER
AND THE PIE MAKER'S FATHER,

13:25.413 --> 13:27.850
DWIGHT PERFORMED TASKS
OF PEACE ENFORCEMENT

13:27.894 --> 13:29.504
AND, IN THE PROCESS,

13:29.547 --> 13:32.724
LEARNED MANY THINGS
ABOUT HIS BROTHERS-IN-ARMS --

13:32.768 --> 13:36.380
SOME THINGS LILY
WOULD RATHER HE NOT KNOW.

13:36.424 --> 13:38.643
CHARLES KEPT A PICTURE OF YOU.

13:38.687 --> 13:42.038
YOU WERE A MERMAID SITTING IN
THE CRADLE OF A GIANT FISHHOOK

13:42.082 --> 13:44.693
WITH A CLAMSHELL BRASSIERE
AND...

13:44.736 --> 13:47.087
[ Laughing ]
...THE TAIL OF A MACKEREL.

13:47.130 --> 13:49.089
I DON'T THINK
WE WERE EVER MACKERELS.

13:49.132 --> 13:50.655
OH, YOU WERE ALWAYS
A MACKEREL.

13:50.699 --> 13:52.440
WHENEVER I SAW THAT PICTURE,
I'D SAY --

13:52.483 --> 13:54.485
"HOLY MACKEREL."

13:54.529 --> 13:56.748
YEAH, I HEARD THAT ONE COMING
FROM AROUND THE CORNER.

13:56.792 --> 13:58.881
IT WAS WEARING TAP SHOES.

13:58.925 --> 14:01.318
CHARLES NEVER TOLD ME
YOU WERE WITTY!

14:01.362 --> 14:04.104
IT'S PROBABLY THE ONLY THING
HE NEVER TOLD ME ABOUT YOU.

14:04.147 --> 14:07.150
BOY, DID HE TALK...
ABOUT YOU --

14:07.194 --> 14:08.978
WHEN HE WASN'T TALKING ABOUT
THIS ONE,

14:09.022 --> 14:11.285
WHICH WAS 99.9%
OF THE TIME.

14:11.328 --> 14:13.635
I'M QUITE
THE CONVERSATION PIECE.

14:13.678 --> 14:15.245
WHEN YOU OPENED THAT DOOR,

14:15.289 --> 14:18.988
I GOT A "ROCK 'EM SOCK 'EM
ROBOT" POW TO THE CHIN.

14:19.032 --> 14:21.730
NOW I KNOW WHY CHARLES
ALWAYS REGRETTED

14:21.773 --> 14:25.038
LETTING ANOTHER WOMAN
COME BETWEEN THE TWO OF YOU.

14:25.081 --> 14:26.953
HE BROKE MY HEART.

14:26.996 --> 14:28.693
CHARLES BROKE A LOT OF HEARTS,

14:28.737 --> 14:31.131
BUT HE ONLY
GOT HIS BROKEN ONCE.

14:31.174 --> 14:32.610
KNOCKED HIM FOR A DOOZY, TOO.

14:32.654 --> 14:34.438
UM, DO YOU HAVE A POINT
TO THIS VISIT,

14:34.482 --> 14:37.224
OR DID YOU JUST STOP BY
FOR SNORTS AND GIGGLES?

14:37.267 --> 14:39.530
THE SNORTS AND GIGGLES
ARE THE RAISINS IN MY OATMEAL.

14:39.574 --> 14:40.923
NO, I'M HERE FOR SOMETHING --

14:40.967 --> 14:43.317
A COMMON BRASS POCKET WATCH.

14:43.360 --> 14:44.840
IT BELONGED TO CHARLES,

14:44.884 --> 14:48.017
HENCE IT HAD A "C.C."
ENGRAVED ON THE BACK.

14:48.061 --> 14:51.629
IT LOOKED A LOT LIKE THIS ONE,
WHICH IS MINE, HENCE THE "D.D."

14:51.673 --> 14:53.370
WE ALL GOT THEM WHEN WE WERE
IN THE SERVICE TOGETHER.

14:53.414 --> 14:54.937
I DON'T RECALL
A POCKET WATCH.

14:54.981 --> 14:56.199
HMM.
VIVIAN, MAYBE --

14:56.243 --> 14:57.940
SHE DOESN'T RECALL,
EITHER.

14:57.984 --> 14:59.550
WELL...
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

14:59.594 --> 15:01.074
POCKET WATCH
OR NO POCKET WATCH,

15:01.117 --> 15:04.686
I THINK I CAN TELL
WHEN IT'S TIME FOR ME TO GO.

15:04.729 --> 15:06.644
I'LL GET YOUR COAT.THANK YOU.

15:08.820 --> 15:11.780
I'M NOT GONNA SAY
ANYTHING TO VIVIAN
ABOUT WHAT YOU DID TO HER.

15:11.823 --> 15:13.216
THAT WOULD BE CRUEL.

15:13.260 --> 15:14.565
NOT AS CRUEL
AS WHAT YOU DID,

15:14.609 --> 15:16.393
BUT NO NEED TO QUANTIFY
YOUR SISTER'S PAIN.

15:16.437 --> 15:18.613
HEY, DON'T COME FOR ME,
FELLA. I FIGHT DIRTY.

15:18.656 --> 15:20.180
I DON'T WANT TO FIGHT.

15:20.223 --> 15:22.443
I NEED TO CHANGE
YOUR PERCEPTION OF ME.

15:22.486 --> 15:24.227
LET'S SIT DOWN AND
TEAR A PHEASANT TOGETHER --

15:24.271 --> 15:25.707
YOU, ME, AND YOUR SISTER.

15:25.750 --> 15:27.013
IF I EVER SEE YOU AGAIN,

15:27.056 --> 15:28.492
IT WON'T BE PHEASANT
I'LL BE TEARING.

15:28.536 --> 15:33.541
OH, TABASCO.
YOU SURE ARE A SPICY COCKTAIL.

15:33.584 --> 15:36.022
Narrator: WHILE LILY
WAS GIVING DWIGHT THE STINK-EYE

15:36.065 --> 15:37.980
WITH THE ONLY EYE SHE HAD,

15:38.024 --> 15:42.985
HER SISTER, VIVIAN, HAD SET HER
EYES ON SOMETHING MUCH SWEETER,

15:43.029 --> 15:48.512
A CONFECTION SHE HADN'T TASTED
IN QUITE SOME TIME...

15:48.556 --> 15:49.992
...A DATE.

15:55.041 --> 15:56.999
AS THE GREAT HERRMANN
TOOK TO THE STAGE

15:57.043 --> 15:58.914
FOR HIS SECOND PERFORMANCE
OF THE NIGHT...

15:58.958 --> 16:00.872
NOW YOU SEE ME...

16:05.442 --> 16:08.532
...A MURDER INVESTIGATION
WAS BEING PERFORMED

16:08.576 --> 16:11.492
UNDER THE PROSCENIUM ARCH
OF HIS DRESSING ROOM.

16:11.535 --> 16:13.276
POOR MERCURY.

16:13.320 --> 16:15.670
OH, I WISH YOU COULD TELL US
WHO DID YOU IN.

16:15.713 --> 16:17.193
Ned:
HE'S A MONKEY.

16:17.237 --> 16:19.239
BARRING AND EVOLUTIONARY LEAPS
YET UNHEARD OF,

16:19.282 --> 16:21.023
THE MONKEY CAN'T TALK.

16:21.067 --> 16:23.591
WELL, HE'S ALSO DEAD, WHICH IS
WHY HE REALLY CAN'T TALK.

16:23.634 --> 16:25.593
THAT'S TRUE, TOO.
Chuck: ALICE CAN TALK.

16:25.636 --> 16:28.248
SHE'S GOT BURNS ON HER LIPS
AND ULCERS ON HER TONGUE.

16:28.291 --> 16:30.119
SHE'S TELLING US
THAT SHE WAS POISONED.

16:30.163 --> 16:32.730
WE GOT A MONKEY
FLATTENED BY A SANDBAG.

16:32.774 --> 16:35.124
MEANS THE KILLER KNOWS
THEIR WAY AROUND BACKSTAGE.

16:35.168 --> 16:36.996
WE'VE GOT TWO DOVES
IMPALED BY BAD TASTE

16:37.039 --> 16:39.215
AND A MALFUNCTIONING COAT GAG.

16:39.259 --> 16:41.391
KILLER KNOWS HOW THE GREAT
HERRMANN'S TRICKS WORK.

16:41.435 --> 16:44.699
I THINK ALICE ATE THE LETTUCE
OFF THE GREAT HERRMANN'S BLT.

16:44.742 --> 16:46.483
KILLER KNOWS
HOW TO MAKE A SANDWICH.

16:46.527 --> 16:48.268
YEAH, THE LETTUCE WAS SUPPOSED
TO STAY ON THE SANDWICH

16:48.311 --> 16:50.270
AND BE EATEN
BY THE GREAT HERRMANN.

16:50.313 --> 16:52.533
THE FALLING SANDBAG,
THE RIGGED JACKET.

16:52.576 --> 16:54.056
THE KILLER WASN'T TRYING
TO KILL ANIMALS.

16:54.100 --> 16:56.406
KILLER WAS TRYING TO KILL
THE GREAT HERRMANN.

16:56.450 --> 16:58.887
[ SCREAMING, CROWD MURMURING ]

17:04.675 --> 17:06.329
HE DIDN'T GET OUT!

17:06.373 --> 17:08.592
HE DIDN'T GET OUT!

17:08.636 --> 17:09.724
NO!

17:09.767 --> 17:11.117
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

17:13.989 --> 17:15.730
ISN'T IT FUNNY HOW EASY IT IS
TO REMAIN CALM

17:15.773 --> 17:17.514
WHEN EVERYONE ELSE
IS FREAKING OUT?

17:17.558 --> 17:18.950
[ SCREAMS ]

17:23.433 --> 17:25.261
Narrator:
SADLY, THE GREAT HERRMANN

17:25.305 --> 17:28.264
HAD FAILED TO ESCAPE
HIS GREAT ESCAPE.

17:28.308 --> 17:31.876
HIS UNTIMELY EXPIRATION
WAS DEEMED BY THE AUTHORITIES

17:31.920 --> 17:35.489
TO BE ACCIDENTAL DEATH
DUE TO AGGRAVATED "CEMENTIA."

17:35.532 --> 17:37.230
Ralston:
THIS WASN'T AN ACCIDENT.

17:37.273 --> 17:40.102
THE GREAT HERRMANN PERFORMED
THAT TRICK A THOUSAND TIMES.

17:40.146 --> 17:42.017
WHAT DID HE DO
WITH ALL THOSE CEMENT BLOCKS?

17:42.061 --> 17:44.150
DONATED THEM TO THE PAPEN COUNTY
MARINE INSTITUTE

17:44.193 --> 17:45.629
TO CREATE ARTIFICIAL REEFS.

17:45.673 --> 17:47.370
THE GREAT HERRMANN
HAD A DEDICATED FAN BASE

17:47.414 --> 17:49.416
OF BARNACLES, CORALS,
AND OYSTERS.

17:49.459 --> 17:54.421
WELL, TONIGHT THE INVERTEBRATES
OF THE SEA WILL MOURN HIS LOSS.

17:54.464 --> 17:55.944
Olive: POOR HERMANN.

17:55.987 --> 17:58.164
FRED AND GINGER
AND ALICE AND MERCURY --

17:58.207 --> 17:59.774
I WANT THEM ALL AVENGED!

17:59.817 --> 18:01.428
I'M SORRY, BUT NOW THAT
EVERYONE'S CALMED DOWN,

18:01.471 --> 18:03.517
I'M FREAKING OUT.

18:03.560 --> 18:05.823
I THINK
IT'S THE ANIMAL CRUELTY.

18:05.867 --> 18:07.521
DON'T FREAK OUT.
I KNOW A DOG AND A PIG

18:07.564 --> 18:09.392
THAT HAVEN'T BEEN IMPALED,
POISONED, OR BLUDGEONED

18:09.436 --> 18:11.133
THAT NEED TO BE FED,
LOVED, AND WALKED.

18:11.177 --> 18:14.005
AWW, MAYBE I'LL GO DO THAT
RIGHT NOW.

18:14.049 --> 18:17.183
I'M SORRY ABOUT YOUR
NEXT-BEST-THING MAGIC DAD.

18:17.226 --> 18:19.185
AND I'M...

18:19.228 --> 18:20.969
I'M SORRY ABOUT YOURS, TOO.

18:21.012 --> 18:21.970
UH...

18:25.104 --> 18:26.583
HE WASN'T MY --
HE DIDN'T --

18:26.627 --> 18:29.673
WE DIDN'T HAVE
THAT KIND OF RELATIONSHIP.

18:29.717 --> 18:32.633
ALTHOUGH HE DID PUT HIS HAND ON
MY SHOULDER AND CALLED ME "SON,"

18:32.676 --> 18:35.201
WHICH FELT LIKE
SOMEONE RUBBED THEIR FEET
ACROSS A SHAG RUG

18:35.244 --> 18:37.594
AND REACHED INTO MY CHEST
AND GAVE MY HEART
A STATIC-ELECTRIC POP.

18:37.638 --> 18:40.162
I ALWAYS LOVED
THAT STATIC-ELECTRIC POP.

18:40.206 --> 18:42.208
IT'S ALL VERY CONFUSING.

18:42.251 --> 18:43.992
THERE'S MURDERED MAGIC DADS

18:44.035 --> 18:47.213
AND THE PROMISE OF TASTY PATE
WITH TUNA SAUCE.

18:47.256 --> 18:48.823
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU WERE SAYING IN YOUR HEAD?

18:48.866 --> 18:50.477
'CAUSE THAT AIN'T
WHAT CAME OUT OF YOUR MOUTH.

18:50.520 --> 18:54.524
WHAT I'M SAYING...
I NEED TO SAY TO THEM.

18:56.831 --> 18:59.312
I'M GONNA TAKE CARE OF THIS.
HERRMANN WILL BE AVENGED.

18:59.355 --> 19:00.791
I DON'T MEAN VIGILANTE JUSTICE,

19:00.835 --> 19:02.663
BECAUSE WHAT KIND OF EXAMPLE
WOULD THAT BE?

19:02.706 --> 19:05.318
I MEAN REGULAR GO-TO-JAIL-
FOR-YOUR-CRIMES JUSTICE.

19:05.361 --> 19:08.582
YOU GONNA KICK SOMEONE'S ASS,
FRERE PIE MAKER?

19:08.625 --> 19:10.410
YES.

19:10.453 --> 19:12.629
I'M GONNA KICK SOMEONE'S ASS.

19:12.673 --> 19:14.675
Narrator: AND THE ASS-KICKING
WOULD COMMENCE

19:14.718 --> 19:17.591
WITH THE ASS
THAT POURED THE CEMENT.

19:17.634 --> 19:19.245
I GAVE HERRMANN PLENTY OF TIME
TO GET OUT.

19:19.288 --> 19:21.029
THEN WHY DIDN'T HE GET OUT?I DON'T KNOW.

19:21.072 --> 19:22.465
IT'S PRETTY CRAMPED IN THERE.

19:22.509 --> 19:24.119
MAYBE HE GOT A BLOOD CLOT
AND PASSED OUT.

19:24.163 --> 19:25.338
HOW'D HE USUALLY
GET OUT?

19:25.381 --> 19:26.991
HE DOESN'T TELL ME
THAT STUFF.

19:27.035 --> 19:28.906
THE MONKEY KNOWS MORE
ABOUT HIS TRICKS THAN I DO.

19:28.950 --> 19:30.952
YOU MEAN THE DEAD MONKEY?YES, THE DEAD MONKEY.

19:30.995 --> 19:33.172
WHAT, ARE YOU GONNA TRY
AND PIN THAT ONE ON ME, TOO?

19:33.215 --> 19:35.348
WHAT ABOUT FRED AND GINGER?DON'T FORGET THE RABBIT.

19:35.391 --> 19:37.393
ALICE WAS THE ONLY ONE
I LIKED.

19:37.437 --> 19:38.960
DAMN MONKEY WAS MEAN.

19:39.003 --> 19:41.789
AND THOSE BIRDS --
THOSE HORRIBLE BIRDS.

19:41.832 --> 19:44.270
EVERY TIME THEY'D FLY OUT OF HIS
POCKETS, THEY'D ATTACK MY WEAVE.

19:44.313 --> 19:46.141
SO WHEN ANIMALS ATTACK,
YOU ATTACK BACK,

19:46.185 --> 19:47.925
THEN KILL THE GUY
WHO TRAINED THEM TO ATTACK.

19:47.969 --> 19:51.973
NO, I STAND THERE HUMILIATED
BY A MEAN MONKEY

19:52.016 --> 19:54.454
NIGHT AFTER NIGHT
FOR EIGHT YEARS.

19:54.497 --> 19:56.586
I TOLD MYSELF NO MORE THAN
THREE, BUT IT'S BEEN EIGHT.

19:56.630 --> 19:58.240
I STAND THERE, AND I TAKE IT,

19:58.284 --> 20:00.416
HOPING THE GREAT HERRMANN
WILL MAKE GOOD

20:00.460 --> 20:02.897
ON THE CARROT HE'S BEEN DANGLING
AND GIVE ME MY OWN ACT.

20:02.940 --> 20:04.333
EIGHT YEARS
OF CARROT-DANGLING

20:04.377 --> 20:05.639
WHILE THE BOBBSEY TWINS
PASS YOU BY?

20:05.682 --> 20:07.336
HONEY, YOU BEEN SPURNED,

20:07.380 --> 20:08.642
AND NEXT TO
THE SPURNED LOVER,

20:08.685 --> 20:10.731
THE SPURNED EMPLOYEE
RIDES SHOTGUN

20:10.774 --> 20:12.733
ON THE HOMICIDE
CHUCK WAGON.

20:12.776 --> 20:15.039
HERRMANN AND ANYONE HE SHARED
A STAGE WITH HAS ENDED UP DEAD,

20:15.083 --> 20:16.389
EXCEPT YOU.

20:16.432 --> 20:19.174
WHICH MEANS YOU'RE
THE KILLER...KILLER.

20:19.218 --> 20:22.308
OR...I'M NEXT.

20:22.351 --> 20:25.398
OR IT WAS AN ACCIDENT,
AND NO ONE'S NEXT.

20:25.441 --> 20:27.487
ALSO, YOU'RE WRONG.

20:27.530 --> 20:31.012
SOMEONE ELSE SHARED THE STAGE
WITH THE GREAT HERRMANN --

20:31.055 --> 20:33.014
THE GEEK.

20:33.057 --> 20:36.496
SO, YOU LIKE THE COMIC BOOKS
AND ACTION FIGURES?

20:36.539 --> 20:38.367
HE'S THE KIND THAT BITES
THE HEADS OFF CHICKENS.

20:38.411 --> 20:40.500
Geek: OH, ANIMAL-RIGHTS GROUPS
PUT A STOP

20:40.543 --> 20:43.242
TO THAT KIND OF GEEK
A LONG TIME AGO.

20:43.285 --> 20:46.593
PERFORMERS DRESSING UP AS
SAVAGES AND EATING LIVE ANIMALS.

20:46.636 --> 20:49.683
IT'S TACKY AND A SUREFIRE WAY
TO ALIENATE YOUR AUDIENCE.

20:49.726 --> 20:51.554
I EAT GLASS AND NAILS

20:51.598 --> 20:54.514
AND REGURGITATE
FISH, FROGS, AND MICE.

20:54.557 --> 20:56.298
I'M WORKING MY WAY UP
TO A KITTEN.

20:56.342 --> 20:59.519
REGURGITATING A KITTEN?
THAT'S A UNIQUE TALENT.

20:59.562 --> 21:02.565
I TRAINED MY BODY
TO DO THE EXTRAORDINARY.

21:02.609 --> 21:05.002
MY FIRST JOB WAS AS A PLANT
IN HERRMANN'S AUDIENCE.

21:05.046 --> 21:06.743
THAT'S HOW WE MET.

21:06.787 --> 21:09.572
HE'D PRETEND TO HYPNOTIZE ME,
AND THEN, UNDER HIS SPELL,

21:09.616 --> 21:11.966
I'D DRINK A BOTTLE OF BEER
AND THEN EAT THE BOTTLE.

21:12.009 --> 21:13.794
WE WERE LIKE
A FATHER-AND-SON ACT.

21:13.837 --> 21:16.318
[ GROANS ]
Emerson: WHAT WERE YOU
AND YOUR TUMMY DOING

21:16.362 --> 21:18.320
WHEN HERRMANN WAS ON STAGE
GETTING CEMENTED?

21:18.364 --> 21:19.756
I WAS WALKING THE CROWD.

21:19.800 --> 21:21.932
I PICKPOCKET
RINGS, WATCHES, AND KEYS

21:21.976 --> 21:24.283
AND THEN REGURGITATE THEM LATER
IN MY ACT.

21:24.326 --> 21:26.894
WITH ALL THAT HAPPENED, I FORGOT
TO GIVE SOME OF THEM BACK.

21:26.937 --> 21:29.026
LISTEN FOR YOURSELF.

21:29.070 --> 21:30.593
[ WATCH TICKING ]

21:30.637 --> 21:31.812
OH.

21:31.855 --> 21:33.901
UM, DID YOU
SWALLOW A MAGNET?

21:33.944 --> 21:36.860
SOMEBODY MUST'VE HAD ONE
IN THEIR POCKET.

21:36.904 --> 21:39.210
THAT'S AN AMAZING TALENT,
MISTER GEEK.

21:39.254 --> 21:40.647
HERRMANN WAS THE ONLY ONE
AROUND HERE

21:40.690 --> 21:42.475
WHO HAD ANY RESPECT
FOR MY CONTRIBUTION.

21:42.518 --> 21:44.868
ANY IDEA WHY HE COULDN'T
GET OUT OF THAT BOX?

21:44.912 --> 21:48.263
CAN'T SAY. I BET THE GREAT
HERRMANN IS IN THERE RIGHT NOW

21:48.307 --> 21:51.179
STRIKING SOME
"LAST DAYS OF POMPEII" POSE

21:51.222 --> 21:53.747
THAT'S GONNA TELL YOU EVERYTHING
YOU NEED TO KNOW.

21:53.790 --> 21:56.402
Narrator:
WHILE THE INVESTIGATORS
CONTINUED TO PONDER

21:56.445 --> 21:59.230
WHY THE GREAT HERRMANN
DID NOT GET OUT...

22:01.581 --> 22:06.237
...OLIVE SNOOK WAS ABOUT TO
PONDER HOW SOMEONE ELSE DID.

22:06.281 --> 22:07.282
[ DOOR OPENS, BELLS RING ]

22:07.326 --> 22:09.763
WE'RE CLOSED.

22:09.806 --> 22:11.504
VIVIAN! YOU'RE OUT!

22:11.547 --> 22:14.245
I THOUGHT WE'D AGREED YOU'D CALL
BEFORE DROPPING BY UNEXPECTEDLY,

22:14.289 --> 22:16.160
WHICH WOULD HAVE BEEN EXPECTED
HAD YOU CALLED.

22:16.204 --> 22:17.727
Vivian: I COULDN'T RISK
SENDING A MESSAGE

22:17.771 --> 22:19.468
AND LILY INTERCEPTING IT.

22:19.512 --> 22:21.688
THIS HAS TO BE COVERT.

22:21.731 --> 22:25.996
I'M ON A DATE...
WITH A MAN.

22:26.040 --> 22:27.868
OH. EVENING.

22:27.911 --> 22:30.784
[ PIGBY SNORTS ]
EVENING.

22:30.827 --> 22:33.526
Dwight:
WE WALKED OUT OF THAT SANDSTORM
WITH OUR BOOTS, OUR BERETS,

22:33.569 --> 22:36.877
AND OUR POCKET WATCHES
WITH NO POCKETS TO PUT THEM IN.

22:36.920 --> 22:38.748
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

22:38.792 --> 22:41.621
WE MADE A SPIT PACT,
LIKE IN THE BOY SCOUTS.

22:41.664 --> 22:44.624
LAST ONE ALIVE AND
KICKING TAKES THEM
WATCHES INTO THE DESERT

22:44.667 --> 22:47.104
AND LETS THE SANDSTORM
CLAIM THEM.

22:47.148 --> 22:50.456
THAT'S SO VERY ROMANTIC
AND POETIC,

22:50.499 --> 22:52.849
AND YOU CERTAINLY TOOK
YOUR TIME TO COME CALLING.

22:52.893 --> 22:54.721
CHARLES HAS BEEN DEAD
FOR 20 YEARS.

22:54.764 --> 22:56.592
I'VE BEEN IN PRISON
FOR 22.

22:56.636 --> 22:59.029
EMOTIONAL OR FEDERAL?I'M GONNA SAY YES TO BOTH.

22:59.073 --> 23:01.031
I CAN ONLY SAY YES
TO ONE.

23:01.075 --> 23:03.904
HMM. MUST SEEM
A LITTLE LESS ROMANTIC NOW.

23:03.947 --> 23:06.036
OH, NO.
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:06.080 --> 23:08.082
ON THE CONTRARY.

23:08.125 --> 23:09.997
I KNEW WHAT KIND OF MAN
CHARLES WAS,

23:10.040 --> 23:11.738
AND THE WAY YOU TELL IT,

23:11.781 --> 23:14.741
YOU BOYS SOUND MORE LIKE BANDITS
THAN PEACE-KEEPERS.

23:14.784 --> 23:17.265
WE WERE A LITTLE OF BOTH.

23:17.308 --> 23:20.094
ABOUT CHARLES'
POCKET WATCH --

23:20.137 --> 23:21.965
I DO RECALL IT.
SO DOES LILY.

23:22.009 --> 23:24.054
I DON'T KNOW
WHY SHE LIED TO YOU.

23:24.098 --> 23:25.926
I THINK SHE JUST WANTED YOU
TO LEAVE.

23:25.969 --> 23:27.580
IF LILY WANTS TO KEEP THAT
WATCH, SHE SHOULD KEEP IT.

23:27.623 --> 23:29.451
OH, SHE DIDN'T KEEP IT.

23:29.495 --> 23:30.931
WE BURIED IT WITH OUR NIECE,

23:30.974 --> 23:33.237
LONELY TOURIST
CHARLOTTE CHARLES.

23:33.281 --> 23:36.240
IT WAS HER FATHER'S.
WE WANTED HER TO HAVE IT.

23:36.284 --> 23:38.242
THAT POOR GIRL MURDERED
ON A TAHITIAN GETAWAY --

23:38.286 --> 23:40.462
THAT WAS CHARLES'
LITTLE GIRL?

23:40.506 --> 23:43.987
LILY IS SENSITIVE
WHEN IT COMES TO CHARLOTTE.

23:44.031 --> 23:46.381
OF COURSE SHE IS.

23:46.425 --> 23:47.556
SHE LOST HER DAUGHTER.

23:47.600 --> 23:49.079
NIECE.
NIECE.

23:49.123 --> 23:50.864
I KNOW WHAT
THE RELATIONSHIP IS.

23:50.907 --> 23:55.259
I'M JUST SAYING, I THINK
YOU BOTH LOST A DAUGHTER.

23:55.303 --> 23:56.739
YOU RAISED THE GIRL.

23:56.783 --> 24:00.308
HOW COULD YOU NOT FEEL
LIKE SHE'S YOUR OWN?

24:00.351 --> 24:04.225
I'M GLAD THE POCKET WATCH
IS WITH CHARLOTTE.

24:04.268 --> 24:07.489
Narrator: BECAUSE NOW HE KNEW
WHERE TO FIND IT,

24:07.533 --> 24:09.099
OR SO HE THOUGHT,

24:09.143 --> 24:11.928
JUST AS OUR PRIVATE
INVESTIGATORS THOUGHT THEY KNEW

24:11.972 --> 24:15.889
WHERE TO FIND
THE GREAT HERRMANN.

24:15.932 --> 24:17.934
WHERE'S THE GREAT HERRMANN?

24:19.849 --> 24:21.285
GIVE ME THAT.

24:23.766 --> 24:25.681
UGH.
NOW YOU SEE ME...

24:25.725 --> 24:27.291
"...AND NOW YOU DON'T.

24:27.335 --> 24:30.425
DOUBLE KISSES, DOUBLE HUGS,
THE GREAT HERRMANN."

24:30.469 --> 24:32.035
SON OF A BITCH.

24:38.346 --> 24:40.435
IT WAS A DISAPPEARING ACT.

24:40.479 --> 24:43.307
NOW YOU SEE HIM...
NOW YOU DON'T.

24:43.351 --> 24:46.267
THE GOOD NEWS IS HE'S
STILL ALIVE... SOMEWHERE.

24:46.310 --> 24:48.008
WHY WOULD THE GREAT HERRMANN
DISAPPEAR?

24:48.051 --> 24:49.183
I'M SURE HE WOULDN'T HAVE
DISAPPEARED UNLESS HE HAD TO.

24:49.226 --> 24:50.837
HE'S AN IMPORTANT MAN.

24:50.880 --> 24:52.882
HE PROBABLY HAD IMPORTANT
MAN MATTERS TO ATTEND TO.

24:52.926 --> 24:54.362
OH.

24:54.405 --> 24:55.972
THAT'S WHAT HERRMANN TOLD US
WHEN DAD LEFT.

24:56.016 --> 24:57.626
THAT'S WHY I SAID, "OH."

24:57.670 --> 24:59.976
IT WAS AN ATTEMPT TO CORRAL
THOSE WORDS BACK INTO MY MOUTH.

25:00.020 --> 25:03.676
WHAT DID HERRMANN TELL YOU
ABOUT WHEN DAD LEFT?

25:03.719 --> 25:06.200
DID HE SAY
WHY DAD HAD TO LEAVE?

25:06.243 --> 25:08.245
HE TOLD ME WHAT HE TOLD YOU.

25:08.289 --> 25:10.987
DID HE TELL YOU ANYTHING
HE DIDN'T TELL US?

25:11.031 --> 25:13.381
THERE MAY HAVE BEEN
SELECT DETAILS.

25:13.424 --> 25:15.165
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

25:15.209 --> 25:16.732
ON A COOL AUTUMN DAY

25:16.776 --> 25:21.084
9 YEARS, 48 WEEKS, 26 DAYS,
AND 7 HOURS EARLIER,

25:21.128 --> 25:22.956
MAURICE AND RALSTON'S FATHER

25:22.999 --> 25:26.437
PROMISED THEM A MAGIC SHOW
THEY WOULD NEVER FORGET.

25:26.481 --> 25:31.007
A NEW MAGICIAN, CLEVERLY BILLED
AS HERMAN GUNT'S MAGIC EXPRESS,

25:31.051 --> 25:34.271
CALLED FOR A VOLUNTEER.

25:34.315 --> 25:37.057
"I'LL BE BACK," DEAR DAD SAID.

25:49.373 --> 25:50.766
[ AUDIENCE MURMURING ]

25:50.810 --> 25:52.202
[ APPLAUSE ]

25:58.861 --> 26:00.123
[ CYMBAL CRASHES ]

26:03.823 --> 26:05.302
Narrator:
THE FLEDGLING MAGICIAN

26:05.346 --> 26:07.522
TRIED TO COMFORT
THE FATHERLESS BOYS

26:07.566 --> 26:09.872
WITH VAGUE BUT IMPORTANT MOTIVES

26:09.916 --> 26:14.398
BEHIND THEIR DEAR DAD'S
DISAPPEARANCE.

26:14.442 --> 26:16.183
THE TWINS' FRAGILE HEARTS

26:16.226 --> 26:19.621
GLADLY BELIEVED
IN THE ILLUSION OF HIS WORDS...

26:19.665 --> 26:22.493
UNTIL NOW.

26:22.537 --> 26:24.147
HE WASN'T AN IMPORTANT MAN.

26:24.191 --> 26:26.280
HE DIDN'T HAVE IMPORTANT
MAN MATTERS TO ATTEND TO.

26:26.323 --> 26:28.325
YOUR DAD...

26:28.369 --> 26:30.589
OUR DAD WAS JUST SOME GUY

26:30.632 --> 26:32.373
DITCHING HIS KIDS
AT A SUNDAY MATINEE.

26:32.416 --> 26:35.942
THAT'S WHAT HERRMANN TOLD ME.
THAT'S WHAT HE DIDN'T TELL YOU.

26:35.985 --> 26:37.552
HE DIDN'T WANT TO HURT YOU

26:37.596 --> 26:39.293
ANY MORE THAN YOU HAD
ALREADY BEEN HURT.

26:39.336 --> 26:40.903
YOU SURE DIDN'T HAVE
A PROBLEM TELLING US.

26:40.947 --> 26:42.470
YEAH.

26:42.513 --> 26:43.776
WELL, IN MY DEFENSE,
YOU BADGERED ME A LITTLE,

26:43.819 --> 26:46.213
AND CONSIDERABLE TIME
HAS PASSED.

26:46.256 --> 26:47.693
I PROBABLY SOUND LIKE
SOME HORRIBLE MISSIONARY

26:47.736 --> 26:49.216
SHOWING UP
AND TELLING THE NATIVES

26:49.259 --> 26:51.566
THEY'RE WORSHIPPING
A FALSE GOD, BUT...

26:51.610 --> 26:54.090
YOU KIND OF ARE.

26:54.134 --> 26:56.919
HE LEFT THREE SONS.

26:56.963 --> 26:58.442
THERE REALLY ISN'T
A GOOD EXCUSE.

26:58.486 --> 26:59.966
DID HERRMANN TELL YOU

27:00.009 --> 27:01.794
RALSTON WET HIMSELF
WHEN DAD DISAPPEARED?

27:01.837 --> 27:03.665
IT WAS YEARS BEFORE WE COULD
PERFORM A DISAPPEARING ACT

27:03.709 --> 27:05.232
WITHOUT HAVING TO USE
A MOP.

27:05.275 --> 27:06.668
WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

27:06.712 --> 27:08.322
I GET ANXIETY-INDUCED
ACID REFLUX

27:08.365 --> 27:09.845
AT THE MERE MENTION OF MAGIC.

27:09.889 --> 27:12.065
RALSTON, YOU WET YOURSELF.

27:12.108 --> 27:14.807
WE'RE TWO GROWN MEN WITH
DAD-RELATED BODY-FLUID ISSUES.

27:14.850 --> 27:16.896
I CAN'T SUCK LOZENGES
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE,

27:16.939 --> 27:18.593
AND YOU CAN'T WEAR
ADULT DIAPERS.

27:18.637 --> 27:20.813
I LEARNED TO CONTROL
MY BLADDER YEARS AGO.

27:20.856 --> 27:23.250
OH.
GOOD FOR YOU.

27:23.293 --> 27:26.557
I KNOW MY ACID REFLUX
IS JUST HEARTBURN,

27:26.601 --> 27:28.516
AND YOUR HEART'S BURNING, TOO.

27:28.559 --> 27:30.257
LOOK AT THE WAY
YOU'RE HOLDING ON TO THAT SCARF.

27:30.300 --> 27:33.739
YOU'RE NOT CLINGING TO HERRMANN.
YOU'RE CLINGING TO DAD.

27:33.782 --> 27:35.654
HOLDING TIGHTER
ISN'T GONNA BRING HIM BACK.

27:35.697 --> 27:37.786
IT'S NOT GONNA BRING
EITHER OF THEM BACK.

27:42.008 --> 27:43.444
WHERE'S THE REST OF IT?

27:43.487 --> 27:44.706
WASN'T IT IN THAT BLOCK
OF CEMENT

27:44.750 --> 27:46.534
WITH HERRMANN'S
"...NOW YOU DON'T" NOTE?

27:46.577 --> 27:50.016
YEAH, IT PROBABLY SHOULD'VE
BEEN, HUH?

27:52.105 --> 27:53.715
THE GREAT HERRMANN IS DEAD.

27:53.759 --> 27:55.674
HE DIED FROM "CEMENTIA"
ON STAGE

27:55.717 --> 27:58.285
WITH THE REST OF THIS SCARF
AROUND HIS NECK.

27:58.328 --> 28:00.591
I KNEW I SHOULDN'T HAVE
CAME IN HERE. I KNEW IT.

28:00.635 --> 28:02.898
I SHOULD HAVE TOOK MY ASS HOME,
TURNED OFF MY PHONE,

28:02.942 --> 28:05.727
AND GOT UP UNDER THE COVERS,
BUT NO.

28:05.771 --> 28:07.555
SOMEONE SWITCHED
THE BLOCKS.

28:07.598 --> 28:09.644
IT'S CLASSIC
SLEIGHT OF HAND.

28:09.688 --> 28:11.733
HERRMANN WAS THAT LITTLE BALL
UNDER THE COCONUT SHELL.

28:11.777 --> 28:13.256
SOMEONE SHUFFLED
THE SHELLS AROUND,

28:13.300 --> 28:15.041
AND WE LOOKED UNDER
THE WRONG ONE.

28:15.084 --> 28:18.697
THERE WERE TWO PERFORMANCES
OF "CEMENTIA," SO TWO BLOCKS.

28:18.740 --> 28:20.133
KILLER SHUFFLES THE BLOCKS,

28:20.176 --> 28:22.048
HIDES THE ONE
WITH HERRMANN'S BODY IN IT,

28:22.091 --> 28:23.745
AND EVERYBODY THINKS
THE GREAT GREAT

28:23.789 --> 28:26.052
JUST DISAPPEARED
INTO HIS DISAPPEARING ACT.

28:26.095 --> 28:28.968
AND NO BODY, NO MURDER.

28:29.011 --> 28:30.926
MAKES FOR A GREAT URBAN LEGEND,
THOUGH.

28:30.970 --> 28:33.624
HOW DO YOU SHUFFLE
A 500-POUND BLOCK OF CEMENT?

28:33.668 --> 28:35.061
FORKLIFT.

28:35.104 --> 28:36.453
ONLY ONE BLOCK OF CEMENT
WAS FORK-LIFTED

28:36.497 --> 28:37.890
OUT OF THE CONJURER'S
CASTLE TONIGHT.

28:37.933 --> 28:39.761
WHICH MEANS THE OTHER ONE
IS STILL INSIDE.

28:39.805 --> 28:41.371
THE SWITCH HAD TO HAPPEN

28:41.415 --> 28:43.417
SOMEWHERE BETWEEN THE STAGE
AND THE LOADING DOCK

28:43.460 --> 28:45.767
WHEN PEOPLE WEREN'T WATCHING
THE BLOCKS TOO CAREFULLY.

28:45.811 --> 28:48.465
Narrator: USING METAL DETECTORS
TO DETECT THE METAL

28:48.509 --> 28:50.903
OF THE SHACKLES WORN
BY THE GREAT HERRMANN

28:50.946 --> 28:53.035
WHILE PERFORMING "CEMENTIA"...CLEAR.

28:53.079 --> 28:55.908
"TWO FOR THE SHOW,"
FEATURING OLIVE SNOOK,

28:55.951 --> 28:57.910
BEGAN THEIR SEARCH
AT THE LOADING DOCK.

28:57.953 --> 29:00.173
WELL, I ALWAYS LOVED
A GOOD TREASURE HUNT.

29:00.216 --> 29:02.915
Narrator:
THE PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR,
THE PIE MAKER, AND CHUCK

29:02.958 --> 29:05.395
BEGAN THEIR SEARCH
UNDER THE STAGE.

29:05.439 --> 29:07.006
IT MIGHT NOT BE THE CEMENT
THAT KILLED HIM.

29:07.049 --> 29:09.095
WE COULD CHISEL OPEN THAT BLOCK
AND FIND A MURDER WEAPON,

29:09.138 --> 29:11.140
LIKE A MOJAVE RATTLESNAKE

29:11.184 --> 29:14.100
OR A HIDDEN HYPODERMIC NEEDLE
THAT THE GREAT HERRMANN

29:14.143 --> 29:16.276
UNKNOWINGLY INJECTED HIMSELF
WITH WHILST CONTORTING.

29:16.319 --> 29:19.496
OR WE COULD CHISEL OPEN
THAT BLOCK AND FIND
HE DROWNED IN CEMENT.

29:19.540 --> 29:21.411
WELL, WHEN WE DO
CHISEL IT OPEN,

29:21.455 --> 29:22.804
IT'S TOO BAD
MAURICE AND RALSTON

29:22.848 --> 29:25.285
CAN'T TALK
TO THE GREAT HERRMANN.

29:25.328 --> 29:27.374
THEY DIDN'T GET A CHANCE
TO SAY GOODBYE.

29:27.417 --> 29:29.071
THE BOOHOO BOSOM
DONE DRIED UP.

29:29.115 --> 29:32.640
WELL, MY BOOHOO BOSOM IS PLUMP
AND BRIMMING WITH MILK.

29:32.683 --> 29:33.989
UGH.

29:34.033 --> 29:35.643
A SMALL CONVERSATION
CAN GO A LONG WAY,

29:35.686 --> 29:37.514
EVEN UNDER THE FALSEST
OF PRETENSES.

29:37.558 --> 29:39.734
Ned: HAVE YOU BEEN
CRANK-CALLING LILY AGAIN?

29:39.778 --> 29:41.910
MM, NOT RECENTLY...

29:41.954 --> 29:45.392
ALTHOUGH THAT DOES DEPEND
ON HOW YOU DEFINE "RECENTLY."

29:45.435 --> 29:47.046
WOMAN, DON'T YOU KNOW
PEOPLE HAVE CALLER I.D.?

29:47.089 --> 29:48.787
[ RAPID BEEPING ]
OH, OH!

29:48.830 --> 29:50.963
THERE'S SOMETHING
UNDERNEATH THESE FLOORBOARDS.

29:56.707 --> 29:58.927
Ned:
I GIVE YOU "CEMENTIA."

29:58.971 --> 30:00.842
HERRMANN SLID
RIGHT OFF THE STAGE

30:00.886 --> 30:03.323
AND DROPPED INTO
THIS STRATEGICALLY
JACKHAMMERED GRAVE.

30:03.366 --> 30:05.325
OUT OF ALL THE WAYS
TO HAVE YOUR BODY STASHED,

30:05.368 --> 30:07.283
THIS ONE'S
NOT SO TERRIBLE.

30:07.327 --> 30:08.807
MAYBE THE KILLER
WANTED THE GREAT HERRMANN

30:08.850 --> 30:10.634
TO BE PART OF
THE CONJURER'S CASTLE FOREVER.

30:10.678 --> 30:12.158
IF THE KILLER
CARED THAT MUCH,

30:12.201 --> 30:13.637
YOU'D THINK HE'D AT LEAST
BREAK OUT HIS TROWEL

30:13.681 --> 30:15.248
AND MAKE THE THING
LOOK NICE.

30:15.291 --> 30:17.859
LOOK AT THOSE EDGES.
HE'S GOT TO FILL THIS ALL IN.

30:17.903 --> 30:20.035
LORD KNOWS THERE'S ENOUGH CEMENT
IN THE HOUSE.

30:20.079 --> 30:22.124
[ FOOTSTEPS ]

30:22.168 --> 30:23.299
[ CREAKING ]

30:23.343 --> 30:25.345
[ WHIRRING ]

30:25.388 --> 30:27.390
DID SOMEONE JUST TURN ON
THE CEMENT MIXER?

30:33.614 --> 30:35.572
MAYBE IT'S OLIVE
AND THE BOYS.

30:35.616 --> 30:37.270
MAYBE WHAT'S
OLIVE AND THE BOYS?

30:37.313 --> 30:38.924
WHOEVER TURNED ON
THE CEMENT MIXER.

30:38.967 --> 30:40.621
YOU FOUND
THE GREAT HERRMANN.

30:40.664 --> 30:42.492
Emerson: WHOEVER DROPPED
THIS BLOCK IN THERE IS BACK

30:42.536 --> 30:45.582
TO MAKE SURE HERRMANN IS PART OF
THE CONJURER'S CASTLE FOREVER.

30:45.626 --> 30:47.149
THAT'S HIS KILLER?THAT'S HIS KILLER?

30:48.934 --> 30:53.155
NO, NO! FOOLS RUSH IN!
WE'RE NOT FOOLS!

30:53.199 --> 30:54.765
OVER THERE!

30:54.809 --> 30:56.680
THEY SPRANG
LIKE ATTACK MONKEYS.

30:56.724 --> 30:59.292
I'LL TAKE CARE OF THEM.
YOU TAKE CARE OF HIM.

30:59.335 --> 31:01.598
DO EITHER OF YOU
HAVE A GUN?

31:01.642 --> 31:03.122
NO.
NO.

31:03.165 --> 31:05.994
I'M GOING WITH EMERSON.

31:06.038 --> 31:07.909
HEY!

31:07.953 --> 31:10.085
DON'T BE GOING AROUND CHASING
MURDER SUSPECTS WILLY-NILLY.

31:10.129 --> 31:12.348
WHAT YOU GONNA DO?
USE YOUR WONDER-TWIN POWERS?

31:15.525 --> 31:17.223
Olive: WAIT FOR ME!

31:17.266 --> 31:18.833
OH!

31:18.877 --> 31:20.095
EMERSON.Emerson: WHAT?

31:20.139 --> 31:21.705
IN HERE.

31:21.749 --> 31:24.534
[ GASPS ]
OH, OH.

31:24.578 --> 31:25.666
IS HE DEAD?

31:25.709 --> 31:27.189
THAT'S THE GEEK.

31:27.233 --> 31:28.974
HE EATS GLASS
AND SWALLOWS SMALL ANIMALS.

31:29.017 --> 31:30.714
WHAT'S THAT UP HIS NOSE?

31:30.758 --> 31:33.195
MAYBE IT'S A SMALL ANIMAL
TRYING TO CRAWL TO FREEDOM.

31:40.463 --> 31:43.249
OH, NO, THAT'S ALL THE WAY
UP IN THERE. HE'S DEAD.

31:43.292 --> 31:45.207
YEAH, HE'S -- HE'S --
HE'S GONE.

31:46.339 --> 31:48.994
[ ALL SCREAM ]

31:49.037 --> 31:51.605
YOU KILLED HERRMANN,
BURIED HIM IN THE FLOOR,

31:51.648 --> 31:54.086
AND THEN YOU SNUCK BACK IN HERE
SO YOU COULD SEAL THE DEAL

31:54.129 --> 31:56.131
WITH SOME MORE
OF YOUR CEMENT HANDIWORK.

31:56.175 --> 31:58.133
BUT YOU GOT SURPRISED
BY THE GEEK,

31:58.177 --> 31:59.918
AND THEN YOU KILLED HIM, TOO.

31:59.961 --> 32:01.571
OH, IS THAT HOW
YOU'RE GONNA FRAME ME

32:01.615 --> 32:03.269
AFTER YOU BEAT ME TO DEATH
WITH YOUR METAL DETECTORS?

32:03.312 --> 32:05.140
I AM AN UNARMED WOMAN.

32:05.184 --> 32:07.142
WHY DON'T YOU CALIBRATE THOSE
THINGS TO FIND YOUR MANHOOD?

32:07.186 --> 32:08.883
WELL, IF YOU DIDN'T
KILL ANYBODY

32:08.927 --> 32:10.537
AND YOU AIN'T RUNNING 'ROUND
HERE BURYING BODIES

32:10.580 --> 32:12.408
AND DISPOSING OF WITNESSES,
WHAT YOU DOIN' HERE?

32:12.452 --> 32:14.193
PACKING.

32:14.236 --> 32:17.457
THE UNIVERSE KILLED HERRMANN
TO SEND ME A MESSAGE,

32:17.500 --> 32:18.937
AND THAT MESSAGE
IS THAT EIGHT YEARS

32:18.980 --> 32:20.373
IS LONG ENOUGH TO WAIT
FOR A CARROT.

32:20.416 --> 32:22.114
YEAH, WELL, MY ASSOCIATES

32:22.157 --> 32:24.246
IS OUT DIGGING UP THAT CARROT
YOU BEEN TRYING TO BURY,

32:24.290 --> 32:26.945
AND WE GONNA SEE WHAT THE
UNIVERSE HAS TO SAY ABOUT THAT.

32:26.988 --> 32:30.035
Narrator: AS EMERSON COD
CHISELED AWAY AT HIS SUSPECT,

32:30.078 --> 32:34.604
THE PIE MAKER AND CHUCK CHISELED
AWAY AT THE GREAT HERRMANN.

32:34.648 --> 32:37.172
I LIVE TO AMAZE ANOTHER DAY!

32:37.216 --> 32:39.000
NO, YOU LIVE TO AMAZE
ANOTHER MINUTE.

32:39.044 --> 32:41.481
YOU'VE BEEN CRUSHED BY
"CEMENTIA'S" DEADLY EMBRACE.

32:41.524 --> 32:43.222
I WAS HOPING
THAT DIDN'T HAPPEN.

32:43.265 --> 32:45.006
HOW AM I TALKING RIGHT NOW
AND NOT DEAD?

32:45.050 --> 32:46.007
MAGIC.

32:46.051 --> 32:47.443
IT'S A FAMILY TRAIT.

32:47.487 --> 32:49.010
MUST HAVE GOTTEN THAT
FROM YOUR FATHER.

32:49.054 --> 32:51.273
AND THAT'S SOME POTENT
KUNG FU.

32:51.317 --> 32:53.319
HERRMANN, LOOK, I KNOW
THAT ASKING A MAGICIAN

32:53.362 --> 32:55.451
TO REVEAL THE SECRET BEHIND
HIS GREAT ESCAPE IS VERY RUDE...

32:55.495 --> 32:57.976
THEN DON'T DO IT.
NOBODY LIKES RUDE.

32:58.019 --> 32:59.629
IT COULD HELP US
CATCH YOUR KILLER.

32:59.673 --> 33:02.284
AH.
MAGIC MAN TO MAGIC MAN.

33:02.328 --> 33:03.982
PLUG YOUR EARS.

33:04.025 --> 33:05.984
Narrator:
MAGIC MAN TO MAGIC MAN,

33:06.027 --> 33:10.684
THE GREAT HERRMANN DETAILED THE
FACTS OF THE ESCAPE THAT WASN'T.

33:10.727 --> 33:14.514
IT WAS NOT MAGIC THAT GOT THE
GREAT HERRMANN OUT OF HIS BOX,

33:14.557 --> 33:16.907
BUT A SERIES OF TRAPDOORS.

33:16.951 --> 33:21.129
BUT A MAGNET CONCEALED
IN HIS SHOE WAS NOT UNDERFOOT.

33:24.263 --> 33:25.525
OH!

33:27.570 --> 33:29.050
MAGNETS IN YOUR SHOES?

33:29.094 --> 33:30.617
THAT'S THE SECRET
TO YOUR GREATEST TRICK?

33:30.660 --> 33:32.097
I COULD'VE LIED TO YOU.

33:32.140 --> 33:34.316
TOLD YOU IT WAS FORCE FIELDS
OR TELEKINESIS.

33:34.360 --> 33:36.840
SOMEBODY SNATCHED THE MAGNETS
OUT OF MY SHOES

33:36.884 --> 33:38.277
WHILE I WASN'T WEARING THEM.

33:38.320 --> 33:40.453
DO YOU HAVE ANY LAST WORDS
OR REGRETS

33:40.496 --> 33:43.891
OR SOMETHING YOU'D MAYBE LIKE
TO SAY TO MAURICE AND RALSTON?

33:43.934 --> 33:46.328
SOMETHING I'D LIKE THEM
TO HAVE.

33:46.372 --> 33:48.156
MY FREEZER
HAS A FALSE BOTTOM.

33:48.200 --> 33:50.245
INSIDE, YOU'LL FIND
MY MAGIC BOOK

33:50.289 --> 33:51.986
OF MAGIC TRICKS
AND ILLUSIONS.

33:52.030 --> 33:53.683
GIVE IT
TO MAURICE AND RALSTON.

33:53.727 --> 33:55.120
I'D LIKE TO KEEP IT
IN THE FAMILY.

33:55.163 --> 33:57.035
[ WATCH BEEPS ]
TIME FOR MY NEXT TRICK.

33:57.078 --> 34:00.386
WITH A BIT OF SHOWMANSHIP,
IF YOU DON'T MIND.

34:00.429 --> 34:03.084
NOW YOU SEE ME...

34:03.128 --> 34:05.217
THERE WERE SUPPOSED
TO BE MAGNETS
IN THE GREAT HERRMANN'S SHOES.

34:05.260 --> 34:07.697
THAT'S HOW HE TRIGGERS THE
TRAPDOOR AND ESCAPES "CEMENTIA."

34:07.741 --> 34:10.091
SOMEONE STOLE THE MAGNETS
SO HE COULDN'T ESCAPE.

34:10.135 --> 34:12.572
AFTER HERRMANN DIED,
THERE WERE MAGNETS
IN THE GEEK'S STOMACH.

34:12.615 --> 34:13.834
SO WHAT?

34:13.877 --> 34:15.923
SEW BUTTONS.
HE ATE THE EVIDENCE.

34:15.966 --> 34:17.403
THE GEEK'S THE KILLER.

34:17.446 --> 34:19.753
THE GEEK AIN'T THE KILLER.
THE GEEK IS DEAD.

34:19.796 --> 34:22.234
BLACK MAGIC WOMAN KILLED HIM.

34:22.277 --> 34:23.974
SHE TOOK THAT DANGLING CARROT

34:24.018 --> 34:25.976
AND JAMMED IT
IN THAT DAMN FOOL'S HEAD.

34:26.020 --> 34:28.153
STOP SAYING THAT.
I DID NOT.

34:28.196 --> 34:30.590
Narrator:
IN FACT, SHE HADN'T.

34:30.633 --> 34:33.375
THEY DID NOT JUST LEAVE ME
WITH A DEAD BODY.

34:46.823 --> 34:48.695
RIGHT NOW, I FEEL LIKE
I'M VERY CALM.

34:48.738 --> 34:50.697
YOU ARE. YOU ARE.THANK YOU.

34:50.740 --> 34:53.439
AND I WANT TO STAY THAT WAY,
BUT I NEED YOU
TO STAY CALM, TOO.

34:53.482 --> 34:55.005
SO WHAT'S OUR PROMISE
TO EACH OTHER?

34:55.049 --> 34:57.095
STAY CALM.WHICH MEANS?

34:57.138 --> 34:59.662
NO SCREAMING?YOU'RE WONDERFUL.

34:59.706 --> 35:01.577
I CAN'T WAIT TO LET YOU GO.

35:01.621 --> 35:04.014
Alexandria:
EVERYBODY CAN SEE YOU.

35:04.058 --> 35:05.668
OLIVE,
ARE YOU OKAY?

35:05.712 --> 35:07.366
UM, I'M CALM?

35:07.409 --> 35:09.063
HEY, NERD,
YOU NEED TO GET YOURSELF

35:09.107 --> 35:10.673
A BIGGER HUMAN SHIELD
OR SOMETHING.

35:10.717 --> 35:12.588
YOU HANGING OUT ALL SORTS
OF PLACES I COULD SHOOT.

35:12.632 --> 35:15.069
HOW ABOUT YOU JUST LET
WEE LADY WEE GO?

35:15.113 --> 35:17.419
WELL, I HAVE A GUN, TOO.

35:17.463 --> 35:19.987
I SWALLOWED
A PEARL-HANDLED PISTOL.

35:20.030 --> 35:22.903
I'M COCKING THE TRIGGER WITH
MY STOMACH MUSCLES RIGHT NOW,

35:22.946 --> 35:24.339
AND WHEN IT FLIES
OUT OF MY MOUTH,

35:24.383 --> 35:26.341
IT'S GOING TO SHOOT YOU
IN THE FACE!

35:26.385 --> 35:27.560
I DID HEAR A CLICK.

35:27.603 --> 35:29.475
WAIT.
IT'S A CLICK-CLICKING.

35:29.518 --> 35:31.041
OH, NEVER MIND.
IT'S A WATCH.

35:31.085 --> 35:34.262
YOU AIN'T SHOOTING NOBODY
IN THEIR FACE, TUMS.

35:34.306 --> 35:35.742
YOU ARE NOT GONNA
GET AWAY WITH MURDER.

35:35.785 --> 35:37.700
NED, HE'S GOT A NAIL.

35:37.744 --> 35:39.485
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

35:39.528 --> 35:42.314
THE GEEK, A.K.A. GUNTHER PINKER,

35:42.357 --> 35:44.664
SAW A FATHER
IN THE GREAT HERRMANN

35:44.707 --> 35:48.885
AND A LONG AND HAPPY FUTURE
PERFORMING TOGETHER.

35:48.929 --> 35:51.845
BUT HERRMANN
DID NOT SEE A SON IN HIM --

35:51.888 --> 35:55.544
ONLY A NOVELTY ACT
WHOSE NOVELTY HAD RUN OUT.

36:02.508 --> 36:05.859
HERRMANN HAD CONVENIENTLY
ARRANGED HIS OWN FUNERAL

36:05.902 --> 36:08.470
IN "CEMENTIA."

36:08.514 --> 36:12.822
THE KEYS TO HIS ESCAPE
WERE CONSUMED.

36:12.866 --> 36:14.998
HE MADE THE GREAT HERRMANN
VANISH

36:15.042 --> 36:17.392
AND REPLACED HIM
WITH ANOTHER CUBE.

36:17.436 --> 36:19.307
NO BODY, NO MURDER.

36:19.351 --> 36:21.309
HE INTENDED TO RETURN
WITH HIS TROWEL

36:21.353 --> 36:23.616
AND SEAL
THE GREAT HERRMANN'S GRAVE

36:23.659 --> 36:27.228
WITH THE VERY BRAND OF CEMENT
THAT TOOK HIS LIFE.

36:27.272 --> 36:29.317
I WOULD HAVE EATEN ANYTHING
FOR THAT MAN.

36:29.361 --> 36:31.101
I LOVED HIM LIKE A FATHER.

36:31.145 --> 36:32.755
GUESS HE SHOULDN'T HAVE
CALLED YOUR ACT CHEAP.

36:32.799 --> 36:35.323
THAT FIRST BEER BOTTLE
I ATE FOR HIM WAS A PROMISE,

36:35.367 --> 36:38.326
A PROMISE HE BROKE.
HE TURNED HIS BACK ON ME.

36:38.370 --> 36:41.242
ABANDONED ME LIKE I WAS...
CHEAP.

36:41.286 --> 36:43.331
I WAS ABANDONED BY MY FATHER
WHEN I WAS 9.

36:43.375 --> 36:44.854
I HATED HIM FOR LEAVING ME.

36:44.898 --> 36:46.856
I WROTE LETTERS
TO MY FUTURE SELF,

36:46.900 --> 36:48.510
TELLING FUTURE ME
TO NEVER FORGIVE MY FATHER

36:48.554 --> 36:50.120
AND TO ALWAYS
HOLD A GRUDGE.

36:50.164 --> 36:53.733
THOSE LETTERS WERE LITTLE,
ANGRY TIME CAPSULES.

36:53.776 --> 36:56.431
BUT BEING ANGRY
DIDN'T HELP.

36:56.475 --> 36:59.391
DESPITE WHAT HE DID
TO ME...

36:59.434 --> 37:03.482
I STILL LOVED HIM,
AND I WANTED HIM BACK.

37:03.525 --> 37:04.526
NOW!

37:04.570 --> 37:05.832
HYAH!

37:15.755 --> 37:17.191
TA-DA!TA-DA!

37:17.235 --> 37:19.628
Narrator: THE GEEK,
A.K.A. GUNTHER PINKER,

37:19.672 --> 37:23.545
REGURGITATOR OF FISH, FROGS,
MICE, AND NOW KITTENS,

37:23.589 --> 37:26.548
WAS ARRESTED FOR THE MURDER
OF THE GREAT HERRMANN,

37:26.592 --> 37:28.768
A.K.A. HERMAN GUNT.

37:28.811 --> 37:32.380
WHEN THEY WERE READY, TWIN
MAGICIANS MAURICE AND RALSTON

37:32.424 --> 37:35.078
DEALT WITH THE LOSS
OF THEIR MAGIC DAD,

37:35.122 --> 37:38.299
FINDING HIS BOOK OF SECRETS
WHERE HE HAD LEFT IT.

37:38.343 --> 37:39.779
BUT THEY KNEW THERE WAS SOMEONE

37:39.822 --> 37:42.651
WHO HAD WAITED EIGHT LONG YEARS
FOR THAT CARROT.

37:42.695 --> 37:44.131
WE'LL MAKE YOU
A PHOTOCOPY.

37:44.174 --> 37:45.959
Narrator: AND WITH IT,

37:46.002 --> 37:50.137
ALEXANDRIA THE ASSISTANT WOULD
BECOME THE GREAT ALEXANDRIA,

37:50.180 --> 37:54.141
NEWEST HEADLINER
AT THE CONJURER'S CASTLE.

37:54.184 --> 37:55.577
AS FOR THE PIE MAKER,

37:55.621 --> 37:58.319
HE DISCOVERED
A NEW SIDE TO MAGIC.

37:58.363 --> 38:00.756
MAGIC WAS NOT JUST
WHAT DISAPPEARS,

38:00.800 --> 38:04.020
BUT WHAT REAPPEARS
WHEN YOU LEAST EXPECT IT.

38:04.064 --> 38:06.109
EMBOLDENED
WITH THIS NEW PERSPECTIVE

38:06.153 --> 38:08.416
AND FREE OF THE STING
OF ACID REFLUX,

38:08.460 --> 38:11.550
THE PIE MAKER ARRANGED
A PRIVATE MAGIC SHOW

38:11.593 --> 38:13.029
FOR THE GIRL HE LOVED.

38:13.073 --> 38:15.293
ARE YOU READY?

38:15.336 --> 38:16.816
WELL, IF WE'RE GOING
TO A MAGIC SHOW,

38:16.859 --> 38:19.079
I HOPE YOU'VE GOT
YOUR LOZENGES.

38:19.122 --> 38:20.950
TSK, TSK, TSK.OH, SORRY.

38:20.994 --> 38:23.257
YOU HELPED ME CONQUER
MY LOZENGE DEPENDENCY.

38:23.301 --> 38:26.739
AS TERRIFYING AS IT IS,
MAGIC RUNS IN MY FAMILY...

38:26.782 --> 38:29.959
AND I KIND OF LIKE BEING
FRERE PIE MAKER.

38:30.003 --> 38:32.092
IT'S A NICE FEELING
TO BE ABLE TO TALK

38:32.135 --> 38:34.312
TO THE FAMILY
YOU DIDN'T KNOW YOU HAD.

38:37.140 --> 38:39.229
OKAY, YOU CAN LOOK.

38:39.273 --> 38:40.883
YEAH?

38:40.927 --> 38:42.711
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY.

38:54.984 --> 38:56.377
AWW.

38:56.421 --> 39:00.033
I WANT YOU TO HAVE
THAT SAME NICE FEELING.

39:00.076 --> 39:02.688
DO YOU WANT TO
TALK TO YOUR MOM?

39:02.731 --> 39:05.038
ARE WE GONNA
CRANK-CALL LILY?

39:05.081 --> 39:06.344
IN A WAY.

39:06.387 --> 39:07.736
DING-DONG-DITCH?

39:10.304 --> 39:11.610
HOW?

39:11.653 --> 39:14.134
A SMALL CONVERSATION
CAN GO A LONG WAY,

39:14.177 --> 39:17.964
EVEN UNDER
THE FALSEST OF PRETENSES.

39:18.007 --> 39:21.533
OKAY, NOW THAT VIVIAN
HAS GONE TO BED,

39:21.576 --> 39:24.100
UM, HAVE YOU EVER
ROLE-PLAYED?

39:24.144 --> 39:25.972
OH, I'VE ROLE-PLAYED...
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:26.015 --> 39:27.408
...BUT NEVER IN A CONTEXT

39:27.452 --> 39:29.410
I'D BE COMFORTABLE
ROLE-PLAYING WITH YOU.

39:29.454 --> 39:32.282
OH, NO, NOT -- NOT THAT KIND
OF A ROLE-PLAY.

39:32.326 --> 39:34.981
MORE OLIVES...OLIVE.

39:35.024 --> 39:38.637
THIS IS A WORK-YOUR-GROOVES-OUT
KIND OF A ROLE-PLAY,

39:38.680 --> 39:39.942
NOT GET-YOUR-GROOVE-ON.

39:39.986 --> 39:42.423
OH, OKAY.

39:42.467 --> 39:46.471
YOU'VE TOLD ME THINGS ONLY ME,
YOU, AND THAT NUNNERY
KNOW ABOUT CHARLOTTE.

39:46.514 --> 39:48.908
YOU BEING HER MOTHER
AND NOT BEING HER MOTHER.

39:48.951 --> 39:50.562
THAT AGAIN.

39:50.605 --> 39:53.086
SAY, WHEN YOU WERE A JOCKEY,
DID YOU RIDE THE HORSES

39:53.129 --> 39:54.522
OR JUST BEAT THEM
AFTER THEY WERE DEAD?

39:54.566 --> 39:55.958
I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT
A DEAD HORSE.

39:56.002 --> 39:57.569
I'M TALKING ABOUT
A DEAD DAUGHTER,

39:57.612 --> 39:59.484
AND THAT'S AN AWFUL LOT
OF WEIGHT TO HAUL AROUND.

39:59.527 --> 40:01.224
YOU ARE HARSHING MY BUZZ.

40:01.268 --> 40:03.313
OH, I DON'T WANT TO HARSH.
I WANT TO HELP.

40:03.357 --> 40:06.447
HELP ME HELP YOU
CARRY THE WEIGHT.

40:06.491 --> 40:08.362
OH, LILY,
UNBURDEN YOURSELF.

40:08.406 --> 40:10.712
IF CHARLOTTE WERE ALIVE
RIGHT NOW

40:10.756 --> 40:13.889
AND YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT VIVIAN SETTLING YOUR HASH,

40:13.933 --> 40:16.457
WHAT WOULD YOU SAY TO HER?

40:16.501 --> 40:18.720
IS THIS THE ROLE-PLAY PART
WHERE YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
CHARLOTTE?

40:18.764 --> 40:21.027
YES, AUNT LILY. IT'S CHARLOTTE.
DON'T YOU RECOGNIZE ME?

40:21.070 --> 40:23.029
YOU SHOULD
GET YOUR EYE CHECKED.

40:23.072 --> 40:25.466
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

40:25.510 --> 40:28.513
CHARLOTTE, THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU SHOULD KNOW.

40:33.039 --> 40:34.519
I'M LISTENING.

40:34.562 --> 40:36.085
[ BEEPING ]

40:36.129 --> 40:37.652
I'm your mother.

40:37.696 --> 40:38.653
PRESTO.

40:40.133 --> 40:41.395
GO ON.

40:41.439 --> 40:43.441
ASK YOUR SEA OF QUESTIONS.

40:46.705 --> 40:48.620
SHE CAN HEAR ME?

40:53.320 --> 40:55.844
UM...
THERE'S SO MANY.

40:56.932 --> 40:58.456
I want to know everything.

40:58.499 --> 41:01.546
I WANT TO KNOW EVERY--
EVERYTHING?

41:01.589 --> 41:03.722
EVERYTHING.

41:03.765 --> 41:05.419
START AT THE BEGINNING.

41:05.463 --> 41:08.074
T-TELL ME ABOUT THE --
THE DAY I WAS BORN.

41:08.117 --> 41:13.949
COULD YOU TELL ME
ABOUT THE DAY I WAS BORN?

41:13.993 --> 41:15.821
I WAS AT THE NUNNERY.

41:15.864 --> 41:18.519
IT WAS RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE OF
MID-MIDDLE MORNING PRAYERS.

41:18.563 --> 41:19.999
Sister Mary Mary
came running

41:20.042 --> 41:21.870
with a crucifix and
a bucket of holy water.

41:21.914 --> 41:24.917
She had ideas about the kind of
spawn I was carrying.

41:24.960 --> 41:26.875
BUT...

41:29.704 --> 41:32.664
[ Voice breaking ]
...AFTER YOU WERE BORN...

41:32.707 --> 41:35.580
[ SIGHS ]

41:35.623 --> 41:40.976
...EVEN SHE COULD SEE
YOU WERE AN ANGEL.

41:41.020 --> 41:43.457
Narrator: AS THE ONCE-DEAD GIRL
NAMED CHUCK

41:43.501 --> 41:45.633
HAD HER VERY FIRST CONVERSATION

41:45.677 --> 41:48.288
WITH THE MOTHER
SHE'D ALWAYS THOUGHT DEAD

41:48.331 --> 41:51.160
AND FELT HER HEART GROW FULL...

41:54.990 --> 41:56.426
[ THUNDER CRASHING ]

41:58.124 --> 42:01.214
...ACROSS TOWN,
DWIGHT DIXON WAS VISITING

42:01.257 --> 42:03.999
THE DEAD DAUGHTER
OF HIS DEAD FRIEND...

42:06.567 --> 42:07.960
[ GRUNTING ]

42:11.485 --> 42:14.923
Narrator:
...AND FOUND HER COFFIN EMPTY.

42:16.882 --> 42:18.318
[ THUNDER CONTINUES ]
